cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with improving the spectral efficiency of cellular networks through the joint use of cell biasing and downlink transmit power control. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper investigates the statistical properties of the collection of per-user spectral efficiencies, which involves the study of information transmission and processing. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The use of control mechanisms such as cell biasing and power control to improve network performance falls under the domain of systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with improving the downlink transmission rates in cellular networks, which is relevant to multimedia applications that require high data rates. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper aims to improve the performance of cellular networks in terms of spectral efficiency, which falls under the domain of performance evaluation and optimization.
